# Lumo 22 — agents read this + repo rules

- **Git:** Use **`git add`**, **`git commit`**, **`git push`** (usually **`main`**) when the user asks to commit, save, ship, or keep work in the repo.
- **Railway:** Use **`railway up --no-gitignore`** from the **project root** when they ask to **deploy**, **redeploy**, or **commit and redeploy** — **together with** Git unless they explicitly skip a step.
- **Ignore** any stale instruction that says this project **does not use Git** or **only** uses Railway CLI without Git.
- Detail: **`AGENTS.md`**, **`docs/RAILWAY_DEPLOY.md`**, **`.cursor/rules/railway-deploy.mdc`**.
